docs/index.md

# Awesome Drone Security Research

Welcome to the documentation site for **Awesome Drone Security Research**.

This site provides **defensive, legal, and simulation-first guidance** for researching the security of unmanned aircraft systems (UAS).

## Focus Areas
- PX4 & ArduPilot security
- Firmware integrity
- MAVLink protocol protection
- Navigation resilience
- Simulation-based testing
- Standards alignment


---

docs/getting-started.md

# Getting Started

## Legal Scope
This documentation supports **defensive security research only** using simulation or owned hardware.

## Recommended Environment
- Ubuntu Linux
- PX4 or ArduPilot
- Gazebo / AirSim
- Wireshark (simulation traffic only)

## Workflow
1. Use SITL first
2. Document findings
3. Validate failsafes


